03:21.426 --> 03:22.941
Your girlfriend's dying.

03:23.652 --> 03:26.556
Shouldn't you be spending her
last moments on earth with her?

03:35.889 --> 03:37.483
How are you feeling?

03:37.484 --> 03:39.545
The same as 30 seconds ago.

03:39.570 --> 03:41.195
Not even like a headache?

03:41.452 --> 03:43.483
Oddly enough, I'm getting one now.

03:44.620 --> 03:46.909
I just don't know how you can
think about anything else.

03:46.910 --> 03:49.386
Right now, I feel fine.

03:50.855 --> 03:52.548
- Maybe Barrett was wrong.
- [scoffs]

03:52.573 --> 03:54.249
Barrett's not usually wrong.

03:54.250 --> 03:55.907
Are you trying to make me feel bad?

03:55.932 --> 03:58.101
No! Of course not.

04:00.711 --> 04:02.203
I'm just worried.

04:02.425 --> 04:03.742
Well, I'm not.

04:04.086 --> 04:05.862
I'm not thinking about dying at all.

04:05.887 --> 04:09.380
I'm not... wondering if it hurts

04:10.232 --> 04:13.068
or if I could have
done more while I was alive

04:13.395 --> 04:16.206
or if anyone's gonna think
about me after I'm gone, I...

04:16.748 --> 04:18.709
I'm not wondering what it's like.

04:20.498 --> 04:23.138
One minute you are, and the next...

04:23.722 --> 04:25.130
you just aren't.

04:25.824 --> 04:27.616
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:28.329 --> 04:29.868
I'm not thinking about it at all.

04:29.869 --> 04:31.997
[crying]

04:35.000 --> 04:36.750
Collins didn't bring much with him.

04:36.751 --> 04:39.169
<i>[ominous music]</i>

04:39.170 --> 04:40.936
Let's make sure he doesn't get this.

04:42.507 --> 04:43.633
[clatters]

04:46.803 --> 04:48.095
What's that?

04:48.096 --> 04:50.139
Proof he's not with the government.

04:54.061 --> 04:55.728
Well, that makes more sense, at least.

04:55.729 --> 04:58.147
He works for the company
that made this mess.

04:58.705 --> 05:01.292
I wonder how many others
like him are out there.

05:01.317 --> 05:04.295
<i>[tense music]</i>

05:04.296 --> 05:10.719
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:11.820 --> 05:13.977
I should thank you for injecting me.

05:14.883 --> 05:17.438
There are a million ways
to die in this mess.

05:17.834 --> 05:19.755
Most are pretty awful.

05:22.630 --> 05:26.130
I'll get a bloody nose,
heart'll slow down.

05:26.693 --> 05:28.510
It'll be harder to breathe,

05:29.158 --> 05:30.978
and I'll feel like I'm drowning.

05:31.556 --> 05:34.087
But you'll see it with your
girlfriend soon enough.

05:36.400 --> 05:37.853
Is that right?

05:37.854 --> 05:39.021
[scoffs]

05:39.022 --> 05:41.608
You did a shit job of protecting her.

05:43.291 --> 05:46.299
That's about all you're good
for around here, right?

05:47.626 --> 05:49.324
And you failed.

05:50.075 --> 05:51.363
Mmm.

05:57.082 --> 05:59.674
That poison doesn't have to
be the way you die.

06:01.440 --> 06:03.755
But it is gonna be the way she dies.

06:05.127 --> 06:06.658
And her baby, too.

06:07.217 --> 06:10.219
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:10.220 --> 06:13.138
[both grunting]

06:13.139 --> 06:14.515
- [silenced gunshot]
- Aah!

06:14.540 --> 06:21.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:24.400 --> 06:26.111
[gunshot]

06:30.281 --> 06:31.615
[exhales] Ahh...

06:31.616 --> 06:33.742
- What did you find?
- What do you mean?

06:33.837 --> 06:35.688
Back at the office when you
were going through his pack.

06:35.713 --> 06:37.040
You found something.

06:38.829 --> 06:40.040
Oh, my God.

06:40.041 --> 06:42.985
Shit. Where are they?

06:44.003 --> 06:47.089
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:47.090 --> 06:54.097
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:18.199 --> 07:19.741
Diesel!

07:19.742 --> 07:20.785
[tool clatters]

07:20.810 --> 07:22.365
What happened?

07:22.792 --> 07:24.420
I got the suit.

07:29.007 --> 07:30.675
[exhales]

07:33.761 --> 07:35.470
BARRETT: At least it's not too bad.

07:35.471 --> 07:36.972
Yeah, right.

07:36.973 --> 07:39.266
Doesn't look like the bullet
hit anything crucial.

07:39.364 --> 07:40.528
Thank God.

07:43.605 --> 07:45.314
[sighs]

07:45.315 --> 07:46.716
How you feeling?

07:48.130 --> 07:49.568
I'm fine.

07:49.569 --> 07:51.154
You're lucky to be alive.

07:51.951 --> 07:54.489
I don't feel lucky. He got the gun.

07:54.490 --> 07:56.283
Yeah, but he didn't get the suit.

07:56.284 --> 07:57.611
And he can't leave without it.

07:57.636 --> 07:59.564
We're like sitting ducks in this office.

07:59.589 --> 08:01.454
He's only got four bullets left.

08:02.322 --> 08:03.790
You checked?

08:03.791 --> 08:05.074
Yeah. [grunts]

08:05.457 --> 08:06.793
Well done.

08:06.818 --> 08:08.611
Four bullets can still do some damage.

08:09.136 --> 08:11.902
We're a much harder target
if we're not all together.

08:12.175 --> 08:13.503
I'll hide the suit.

08:15.803 --> 08:17.753
The rest of you, divide up.

08:17.778 --> 08:19.128
Lie low.

08:21.851 --> 08:24.853
<i>[dark music]</i>

08:24.854 --> 08:31.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:37.325 --> 08:39.111
There. How does that feel?

08:39.619 --> 08:40.970
I'm not worried about me.

08:41.245 --> 08:42.577
Guys, keep it down.

08:49.254 --> 08:50.712
Okay, it's all...

08:50.713 --> 08:52.268
Natalie.

08:52.882 --> 08:54.143
Your nose.

08:54.634 --> 08:55.969
[gasps]

09:00.890 --> 09:03.934
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

09:03.935 --> 09:10.942
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:28.251 --> 09:29.252
[gunshot]

09:33.256 --> 09:34.723
Where's the suit?

09:35.113 --> 09:37.552
- I'm getting outta here.
- I‐I don't know.

09:39.762 --> 09:41.096
[gunshot]

09:41.097 --> 09:42.637
I won't ask again.

09:43.599 --> 09:45.037
[muffled whumps]

09:45.062 --> 09:46.272
Ah!

09:50.440 --> 09:52.150
JOHN: [grunts]

09:54.367 --> 09:55.494
Stop!

09:56.018 --> 09:57.283
Right there!

09:58.291 --> 10:00.290
You might wanna listen.

10:00.955 --> 10:03.625
- Don't, please.
- Bring me the suit.

10:03.779 --> 10:05.937
- You have three minutes.
- Okay.

10:06.671 --> 10:07.718
Okay.

10:17.782 --> 10:19.233
Does it hurt?

10:19.427 --> 10:21.970
- Not really.
- Good.

10:23.101 --> 10:24.390
That's good.

10:26.085 --> 10:27.913
Can I get you anything?

10:28.530 --> 10:31.453
I mean, you feel like...
is there something I can do?

10:33.031 --> 10:34.406
Sure.

10:35.304 --> 10:36.749
I'm thirsty.

10:37.632 --> 10:39.476
I can get water.

10:42.825 --> 10:44.577
Be careful.

10:50.625 --> 10:52.959
I think she's more worried than you are.

10:53.454 --> 10:56.048
She does not wanna be left behind.

10:57.259 --> 10:59.142
None of us do.

11:01.677 --> 11:03.420
[voice breaking]
I don't wanna leave you.

11:04.263 --> 11:07.349
<i>[somber music]</i>

11:07.350 --> 11:09.264
It feels so cruel...

11:10.537 --> 11:12.187
that the world would give us something

11:12.188 --> 11:13.730
we never expected...

11:14.714 --> 11:16.009
and then take it away

11:16.034 --> 11:18.386
before we've had any real time together.

11:23.128 --> 11:24.298
Well...

11:25.701 --> 11:27.494
the way I see it is...

11:27.908 --> 11:29.986
all we've had is real time together.

11:30.248 --> 11:32.999
- That's not what I mean.
- Just let me finish.

11:33.166 --> 11:36.237
Look, maybe we haven't had a lotta time,

11:37.713 --> 11:40.658
but the time that we have had,
it's been real.

11:40.987 --> 11:42.886
And it's been honest.

11:43.803 --> 11:45.347
[shaky breath]

11:46.123 --> 11:48.823
And we are who we are in here.

11:54.105 --> 11:55.816
I like who we are.

11:56.941 --> 12:00.068
<i>[somber music]</i>

12:00.069 --> 12:06.993
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:12.206 --> 12:14.607
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:14.632 --> 12:16.170
You two.

12:16.935 --> 12:18.186
Stay.

12:26.919 --> 12:28.121
Put it down.

12:30.465 --> 12:32.363
Grover, don't.

12:34.843 --> 12:36.453
Now, let her go.

12:36.720 --> 12:38.476
Back. Up.

12:39.398 --> 12:40.734
Grover...

12:41.308 --> 12:43.184
You have to let her go.

12:43.185 --> 12:46.229
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:46.230 --> 12:49.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:49.643 --> 12:51.277
Get outta my sight.

12:54.071 --> 12:56.036
If I see any of you before I leave,

12:56.282 --> 12:57.786
I will shoot.

12:58.525 --> 13:00.456
Now, go!

13:12.444 --> 13:14.066
VIOLET: What the hell were you thinking?

13:14.553 --> 13:16.009
I couldn't let him hurt you.

13:16.010 --> 13:17.772
And now we're all going to get killed.

13:19.335 --> 13:20.930
Maybe not.

13:21.587 --> 13:23.267
I made sure he won't get far.

13:25.686 --> 13:28.563
[muffled, soft snarling]

13:28.564 --> 13:32.150
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:32.151 --> 13:34.569
[soft snarling]

13:34.570 --> 13:41.493
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:48.792 --> 13:50.418
[clanging]

13:50.419 --> 13:53.881
[loud snarling]

13:58.632 --> 14:00.555
Is there any sign of him out there?

14:00.804 --> 14:03.333
Not yet. He coulda went out the front.

14:03.560 --> 14:05.308
- What if he's still inside?
- If he's not out there

14:05.309 --> 14:07.130
when it goes off, we're screwed.

14:13.929 --> 14:15.405
Wait... there he goes.

14:16.028 --> 14:17.593
How much time?

14:18.155 --> 14:20.062
Ten, nine,

14:20.347 --> 14:23.567
eight, seven, six,

14:24.145 --> 14:26.013
five, four,

14:26.278 --> 14:28.664
three, two, one.

14:28.665 --> 14:30.416
- [beeping]
- Huh?

14:30.417 --> 14:33.127
[beeping continues]

14:33.128 --> 14:35.129
[grunts]

14:35.130 --> 14:38.801
ALL: [snarling, growling]

14:41.386 --> 14:43.721
[gunshot]

14:43.722 --> 14:46.641
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:46.642 --> 14:50.728
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:50.729 --> 14:54.315
ALL: [snarling, growling]

14:54.316 --> 15:00.863
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:00.864 --> 15:03.827
- ALL: [snarling]
- Aah... aah!

15:04.827 --> 15:11.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:15.367 --> 15:18.734
When I was little, I used to cry
whenever a book ended.

15:19.716 --> 15:21.039
Really?

15:21.758 --> 15:23.109
Any kind of book?

15:24.219 --> 15:25.763
Comedy...

15:26.203 --> 15:27.774
drama...

15:28.633 --> 15:30.945
mystery, historical fiction.

15:31.617 --> 15:33.229
Didn't matter.

15:33.869 --> 15:35.556
I like historical fiction.

15:36.547 --> 15:38.070
Really?

15:38.095 --> 15:39.402
- Yeah.
- [laughs]

15:39.403 --> 15:41.154
[both laughing]

15:41.155 --> 15:44.408
Ah, there it goes.
That's what I was waiting for.

15:46.243 --> 15:47.744
[exhales]

15:49.496 --> 15:51.261
So why'd you cry?

15:53.519 --> 15:55.965
Same reason everyone cries, I guess.

15:59.006 --> 16:02.981
You get to know someone
inside and out...

16:05.596 --> 16:07.228
And then it's just...

16:09.212 --> 16:10.517
the end.

16:12.407 --> 16:14.017
And it's over.

16:18.766 --> 16:20.735
Yeah, but if the story's good,

16:22.321 --> 16:24.079
it sticks with you forever, right?

16:24.281 --> 16:28.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:28.674 --> 16:30.635
You've done so much for me.

16:36.293 --> 16:37.586
[sniffles]

16:38.754 --> 16:40.326
[whispers] I wish I coulda done more.

16:41.873 --> 16:43.287
[whispers] I felt lucky.

16:45.820 --> 16:48.089
In the middle of all of this...

16:51.363 --> 16:52.850
being here with you.

16:52.851 --> 16:55.829
<i>[pensive music]</i>

16:55.830 --> 17:00.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:00.997 --> 17:02.575
[whispers] Yeah, me, too.

17:12.704 --> 17:14.522
I'm gonna be all alone.

17:15.021 --> 17:17.476
No, you're not. You got all of us.

17:17.501 --> 17:20.104
I always spent so much time
being mad at her...

17:20.862 --> 17:22.579
[sniffles] and for what?

17:23.589 --> 17:25.840
[distant thudding]

17:26.236 --> 17:27.623
What the hell was that?

17:28.553 --> 17:32.223
[thudding, clattering]

17:32.224 --> 17:35.393
[pounding, thudding]

17:35.394 --> 17:37.770
[loud thudding]

17:37.771 --> 17:39.906
Everybody back! Go, go!

17:39.930 --> 17:41.106
Oh, my God!

17:41.108 --> 17:44.777
ALL: [snarling, growling]

17:44.778 --> 17:46.737
Aah! Aah!

17:46.738 --> 17:52.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:52.703 --> 17:55.747
[overlapping grunting]

18:00.377 --> 18:01.711
Arghhh!

18:01.712 --> 18:03.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:03.797 --> 18:05.131
Uhh!

18:05.132 --> 18:06.725
Go!

18:12.967 --> 18:14.464
[kids grunting]

18:14.488 --> 18:15.870
They're breaking through!

18:15.895 --> 18:17.393
I don't think we can hold them off!

18:17.418 --> 18:19.830
- DIESEL: We have to fight 'em!
- VIOLET: No! We're gonna lose!

18:19.855 --> 18:21.745
GROVER: We'll just hold
the door... we got it!

18:27.237 --> 18:28.333
Hey!

18:28.822 --> 18:29.905
[snarl]

18:29.906 --> 18:30.948
Over here!

18:30.949 --> 18:33.576
ALL: [growling]

18:33.577 --> 18:35.036
They're backing off.

18:35.037 --> 18:36.482
What's going on?

18:37.068 --> 18:38.294
Where's Natalie?

18:38.833 --> 18:39.874
Oh, no!

18:39.875 --> 18:41.341
- No!
- Go, go!

18:42.502 --> 18:44.837
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:44.838 --> 18:47.423
ALL: [growling, snarling]

18:47.424 --> 18:52.720
<i>[emotional music]</i>

18:52.721 --> 18:59.728
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:18.997 --> 19:21.916
<i>[emotional music, vocalization]</i>

19:21.917 --> 19:29.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:56.952 --> 19:59.954
<i>[vocalization continues]</i>

19:59.955 --> 20:06.670
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:24.438 --> 20:27.314
<i>[emotional music continues]</i>

20:27.315 --> 20:34.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:40.162 --> 20:43.266
LeSean! Oh, my God, is that you?

20:47.377 --> 20:49.030
[crying] We thought you were dead.

20:51.655 --> 20:53.008
They followed me here.

20:54.530 --> 20:56.186
I didn't have a choice.

20:56.636 --> 20:59.680
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:59.681 --> 21:05.145
